title: Seal Was Wrapped Like a Mummy! #shorts
description:
This seal was wrapped like a mummy!
When we found him, he was completely entangled in a pink vegetable sack - from head to tail, tightly cocooned in fine netting. He could barely move, and we still don‚Äôt know how he managed to make it back to shore. Most animals in situations like this never do.
This case shows the ugly reality of plastic entanglement: most affected marine animals suffer and die at sea, unseen. We only get to help the ones that somehow survive long enough to come ashore.
We need real change: stronger legislation against ocean dumping, and a global push to make plastic a valuable resource, not a disposable one.
Until then, stories like this will become more common. Marine wildlife will continue to pay the price.
